###+ 仆1 | _P(')uk(7)_ [[puk1]]

$$
R
  ⼈ + 2
U
  U+4EC6
V
  ==
  - pok3 (per Williams)
  ==
F
  [[Not present]]
W
  ====
  - [[Page~726 仆(8) _P(')ok(8)_ (pok3); here normalised to _P(')uk(7)_ (puk1)]]
    ==
    - This is more often pronounced _~~p(')ok(8)~~ ``p(')uk(7)``_ [[puk1]] than _f(u/)(6)_ [[fu6]]^,
      as given on page~61;
    - _(1)t(i/)n ~~p(')ok(8)~~ ``p(')uk(7)``~~_
        [[din1 puk1 顛仆]]
        slipped down;
    - _(1)k(e/)ung ~~p(')ok(8)~~ ``p(')uk(7)``_
        [[goeng1 puk1 僵仆]]
        fell down stiff, as if dead.
    ==
    --
    [[Reading variation. See $仆fu6.]]
    --
  ====
C
  ==
  - The reading _p(')uk(7)_ (puk1) is not unattested;
    《集韻》 has the reading 普木切, explained 僵也, as an alternative reading
    of the classical word 仆, to fall prostrate (for which see $仆fu6).
  - Williams' reading _p(')ok(8)_ (pok3) is now obsolete, but is interesting to note,
    as it is an alternative expected reading from 《集韻》普木切.
  - The use of 仆 _p(')uk(7)_ (puk1) in 仆街 (see below)
    leads to the perception that the reading is vernacular, even vulgar.
  ==
P
  ++
  1. To fall prostrate.
  ++
E
  ====
  - 【仆街】 (puk1 gaai1)
    ++
    1. To fall prostrate in the street. Informally spelt PK.
       ==
       - 仆你個街 (puk1 nei5 go3 gaai1): "[May] you fall forward [in the] street."
       ==
    ++
    --
    Can be used as an optative, an interjection, an adjective, and a noun,
    varying in meaning from the literal "fall prostrate"
    to the metaphorical "keel over" or "die" (or one who deserves to do so).
    For these, see the [Wiktionary entry for 仆街][wiktionary-仆街].
    --
  - 【仆直】 (puk1 zik6)
    ++
    1. To fall flat on one's face, i.e. to fail utterly.
    ++
  ====
S
  ==
  - $仆fu6
  ==
$$

[wiktionary-仆街]: https://en.wiktionary.org/w/index.php?title=仆街&oldid=87996432
